<p>HUMAN RIGHTS COUNCIL 
Second session 
Agenda item 2 
</p>
<p><b>IMPLEMENTATION OF GENERAL ASSEMBLY RESOLUTION 60/251 
OF 15 MARCH 2006 ENTITLED &#8220;HUMAN RIGHTS COUNCIL&#8221; 
</b></p>
<p><b>Argentina, Canada, Denmark</b>*<b>, Ghana, Netherlands, Nicaragua</b>*<b>,  
Romania, United States of America</b>*<b>:  draft decision 
</b></p>
<p><b>2/&#8230;  Freedom of opinion and expression 
</b></p>
<p> The Human Rights Council, recalling Commission on Human Rights resolution 2005/38 
of 15 April 2005, decides to request the Special Rapporteur on the promotion and protection of 
the right to freedom of opinion and expression to include in his next report to the Human Rights 
Council a focus on journalists, including the issue of security of journalists, in particular in 
situations of armed conflict, taking into account information provided by States and 
intergovernmental and non-governmental organizations, including national press associations. 
</p>
<p>----- 
</p>
<p>                                                 
</p>
<p>*  Non-member States of the Human Rights Council. 
</p>
